A leopard mauled a child to death on Wednesday evening at the Kruger National Park. JOHANNESBURG - A leopard has mauled a toddler to death at the Kruger National Park. It's understood the incident took place at the Malelane Technical Services living Quarters on Wednesday night. The leopard attacked a staff member's child. Chief Executive Officer of South African National Parks Fundisile Mketeni extended his condolences to the family of the deceased. “Our prayers and thoughts are with the family during this trying time, we wish them strength and will give them all the support they need as an organisation," said Mketeni. "It is never easy to lose a loved one, especially under such tragic circumstances." Moral support and professional counselling will be provided to all parties involved, KNP management said.